    },
    {
      "id": "bada0100_847e76e3",
      "file_path": "integrity-monitor/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/im/IntegrityMonitor.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 1776,
      "message": "AFAIK, there is no annotation processor for allSeemsWell, thus there is nothing to enforce the @NotNull annotation.  As a result, if it's fooling sonar into thinking the parameters are non-null, then the annotations should probably be removed.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2018-10-01 20:11:09.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "bada0100_641272b6",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "bada0100_c4f8fe4b",
      "file_path": "integrity-monitor/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/im/IntegrityMonitor.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 1776,
      "message": "I believe the @NotNull does nothing by themselves, they are pretty much documentation I think.   I think it would be safer to just @NotNull from the parameters all together (to correct the sonar) and leave the \" == null\" checks as below.    Not sure how this code works, and if guarantees non-null references to be passed in.",
      "author": {
